Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.map

Interface Map<K,​V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys stored in the map
    V - the type of values that are associated with keys in the map
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<K>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMap, AbstractOrderedMap, SearchTableMap, SkipListMap, UnorderedLinkedMap
    public interface Map<K,​V>
extends java.lang.Iterable<K>
    The Map abstract data type represents a collection of entries, where each entry consists of a 'key' that is mapped to a 'value'. The Map ADT does not allow duplicate keys to exist within the map. All Maps must be Iterable to allow clients to iterate using for-each loops. The Map interface is based on the implementation developed for use with the textbook: Data Structures and Algorithms in Java, Sixth Edition Michael T. Goodrich, Roberto Tamassia, and Michael H. Goldwasser John Wiley and Sons, 2014
    Author:
    Dr. King
